definitions.definition: Proud wife of Cepheus and mother of Andromeda , queen of Ethiopia . When she boasted that her beauty was equal to that of the Nereids , she was punished by Poseidon .
A circumpolar constellation of the northern sky representing Queen Cassiopeia from Greek myth, lying between the constellations Cepheus and Perseus .
